3DCOLORFIT
University of Oxford
Niraj Welikala

07/12/2015

Library dependencies
-----------------
cfitsio
GSL

To run 3DCOLORFIT, do the following:

1) Compile the code galsim3d_gen_models.c
using the Makefile

2) Run the model generation - these generate models with the following Sersic indices for the bulge:
n=4(bulge only), n=4(bulge+exponential disk), n=3.5, n=3, 2.71, 2.56, 2, 1.78, 1.8
./run3dmodels_sim.sh

For each case, we generate bulge and then disk model with the following arguments:
type r0_bulge r0_disk z0_disk bulge_compression Npoints nsersic_bulge

For disk, r0_bulge and bulge_compression are obviously ignored/redundant.


3) Fitting code fit_goods_bvizyjh.c 
Build using the same Makefile

The relevant routines are
make2Dgalaxymodelunconvolved_acs() - generates models without PSF convolution
make2Dgalaxymodelconvolved_acs() - generates models with PSF convolution

